commit 7997dce248bfd4a99199d0783e76c5371e8e5125
Author: Vamsee Achanta <achantav@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 3 22:30:19 2026 -0600

    fix(review): harden all cross-review submit scripts against OOM and timeout failures
    
    This commit addresses several edge cases in submit-to-{claude,codex,gemini}.sh:
    - Clamps file input reading to 5MB to prevent bash OOMs when agents accidentally provide binaries or huge reports.
    - Implements a perl-based cross-platform timeout fallback for macOS environments where GNU coreutils timeout is not installed, preventing orchestrator freezing.
    - Fixes unbound variable crashes when required flag arguments are omitted.
    - Fixes git show commit resolving when the temporary working directory is outside the repo.

